metadata.name: Archiplex — Monochrome #78
metadata.description:
Archiplex Monochrome is a long form generative project, building on the short form Archiplex series. The Archiplex Monochrome algorithm is inspired by Brutalist architecture and design, where expressive forms emerge from the use of textures, materials and structures.

Archiplex Monochrome expands on these Brutalist design elements by floating the central structure of each piece and adding random light sources, introducing unpredictability and elevation to a traditionally structured and grounded art form.

"In this series my subject is the structure: formed yet formless, gravity-bound yet weightless, reflective yet light emitting, unmovable yet malleable."

metadata.name: The Beauty of Discord #59
metadata.description:
This experimental artwork is a unique blend of human and machine inputs, showcasing the potential for collaboration between the two in the creative process. The human component of the piece is evident in the deliberate composition, choice of color, and the use of painting algorithms. Meanwhile, the machine component is represented by two powerful AI technologies. The first, ChatGPT3, generated a thought-provoking poem about the galaxies and cosmos, serving as the inspiration for the piece. The second, DALL-E 2, then used this poem as a prompt to create a stunning AI image, bringing the cosmic themes to life in a realistic and captivating way.

The combination of these two AI technologies, along with the human touch in the painting algorithms and composition, creates an artwork that is truly one-of-a-kind. The final product is not only visually stunning, but it also serves as a glimpse into the future of humanity and the possibilities of AI collaboration in art. The artwork is a testament to the beauty that can result from a seemingly discordant combination of human and machine inputs, and it invites us to consider the impact of technology on the creative process and the role of the human artist in the age of AI.

Artist notes:
Press s to download high-res images.
Press a to see the AI-generated image.
Press g to switch back to the paint.

Read more on the medium website:
shorturl.at/bkqW8

metadata.name: Ticket to Heaven #89
metadata.description:
YOUR NFT TICKET TO HEAVEN
Buy the ticket that will guarantee you the best path to heaven.
Don't worry about your sins anymore:  get an eternal indulgence!
 
INSTRUCTIONS
-Buy your ticket to heaven
-Own this ticket until death without reselling it.
-At the exact instant of death, move your NFT ticket into your physical pineal gland wallet.
-Your GOD's blockchain will automatically recognize your NFT ticket when your soul exits your body to meet  divine judgment.
-Enjoy the trip, you have a reserved place in paradise!

Participate in this art project and buy a ticket for yourself and each of your loved ones. 
Otherwise you will burn in hell.

GENERATIVE TICKET TO HEAVEN
This is the generative version of the "Ticket to Heaven" project for which there are already 573 tickets in three different colors. In addition, 75 crypto artists from all over the world were involved in the original project and decorated some tickets with their style.
 
In the generative version I have taken the three original colors and I have added another 12 color palettes. I kept the green color logic for the VIP pass (which allows you to skip the line in case of mass extinctions) while the tickets with the 7 sins were mixed with the colors of the new palettes.
I added some decorative elements in the watermark and background of the ticket.
 
I used 2 generative algorithms to decorate some tickets, one which incorporates the fractals of the "Fractals and fractures" project and the other which incorporates the rings of the "Scalabili-TREE" project.
 
The profit on the sales of the primary market will be completely directed to the "NFT Spaghetti" community wallet, to finance the contests and community activities
 
Everything is generated with code.
This work uses p5.js library and c2.js library.

 
PROJECT EXPLANATION
“Ticket to Heaven is a metaphor”.
 
People who work with cryptocurrencies live in a new world, with few rules. A dark land where it is easy to commit sins.
The idea of the project is based on the parallelism between religion and blockchain, where access to heaven is governed by a GOD who moves souls from one wallet to another.
 
Blockchain is a new religion. Investing in crypto and NFTs is an act of faith. For many it bears the hope of a more prosperous future, if not for everyone at least for one's self.
 
Buying a ticket to heaven is also an act of faith. 
Take the leap.

metadata.name: Badgirs City #146
metadata.description:
"I used to live in a small city placed at the center of Iran's plateau with the warmest summer days in the country part; spending most of my childhood with my sweet grandma at her old house. She was always keeping her eyes on me not to get heat stroke at noon playing in the yard when the sun was at its peak glowing furiously. Sundays at noon were my favorite, I used to call them “Ice cream” noons sitting beside the nicest person you could imagine and enjoying a delightful ice cream. You won't know how lovely it was to have an ice cream relaxing under the most enjoyable cold breeze of the tallest windcatcher in the city at her house. "



The Badgirs city is the first collaboration between Fleep and IceRain on Fxhash. The concept was established first with the design of a school with a feeling of safe and nostalgia reminding us of the good memories of our childhood as the grandma’s house and the windcatcher for Fleep.
A windcatcher (Badgir) is an Iranian traditional architectural element in the form of a small tower built on the roof of houses in warm locations to create passive cooling. The collection of Badgirs city is a modern recreational development of those traditional windcatchers designed by Fleep and icerain and exquisitely translated into code by Icerain.

Controls:
[1] Set the resolution to Medium Resolution
[2] Set the resolution to High Resolution

metadata.name: CMYK:Unchecked #19
metadata.description:
CMYK:Unchecked offers almost infinite canvases designed to challenge the concept and state of being unverified.

Layout variations include 80 / 40 / 20 / 10 / 5 / 4 / 1 circles. 
Each circle presented is either Cyan, Magento, Yellow or Black.

---

This work is of course a parody of 'Checks' by Jack Butcher presented in a transformative way. The work is in no way related to the original 'Checks' work and is not intended to fool anyone into thinking so thus does not affect the originals market or value.

metadata.name: Reading a book #117
metadata.description:
The formal structure of a book is beautiful by itself, but its aesthetic is the tacit atmosphere within which events take place in a story.

The WebGL real-time animation sets up an initial grid based on the fxhash. The grid cells get subdivided into another grid and the resulting cells become filled with pixels in color (~33%) or black and white (~66%).
The colored pixels come in 3 different coloring styles.
- Big Palette (~49%)
- Small Palette (~49%)
- Monochrome [b/w] (~2%)
4 noise algorithms modify the pixels of selected grid cells while at the same time 4 reset algorithms reassemble the initial image. The selected cells switch over time.

_________________________

Made with p5js.
